WHY CC0 FOR THE DATA LAYER

FAIR (Findable, Accessible, Interoperable, Reusable) practice recommends the
most permissive terms for structured research data, so that other researchers
can reapply the analytical instruments (the Constitutional Legitimacy Vector,
the community-layer coupling scheme) to new cases, and integrate the reform
chronology into comparative datasets, without licensing friction.

